      Subclasses of ModuleException in uniol.apt.analysis.exception 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  MustLeadToSameStateException
      A MustLeadToSameStateException is thrown when two arcs must lead to the same state, but don't.
      class  NoFiniteExtensionPossibleException
      A NoFiniteExtensionPossibleException is thrown when the class ExtendDeterministicPersistent notices that no finite extension is possible.
      class  NonDeterministicException
      A NonDeterministicException is thrown when an analysis needs a deterministic input, but was given a non-deterministic one.
      class  NoSuchTransitionException
      A NoSuchTransitionException is thrown when a user-specified transition does not exist in the given Petri net.
      class  PreconditionFailedException
      A PreconditionFailedException is thrown when the input to an analysis does not satisfy the analysis' precondition.
      class  UnboundedException
      A UnboundedException is thrown when an analysis needs a bounded Petri net as its inbounded but is fed an unbounded system.
